DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Toxic Exposure Specify
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The type of exposure if not listed. Free Form Text
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Retired due to lack of use since the time of curation.  No additional use in classifications or CRFs since created.dmr4.7.2015
DataElementQueryResults.administrativeNotes: 10.17.23_Transferred ownership to support Protocol 000302-C (Natural History Study)_ghd

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Body System Type
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Text term to identify a Review of Systems (ROS) component that consists of one or all members of an organ system, and/or additional medical questions.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: New version with expanded VD and DE using naming standards.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Total Dose Value
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Numeric value for the amount of medicine taken, or radiation given, during a period of time.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: v4.0 replaces v3.0 of the CDE with updated DEC and VD. v3.0 was incorrectly in use as a numeric datatype, but was paired with a (later retired) character VD.  This version pairs the correct VD which is not retired.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Protocol Number
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The numeric or alphanumeric identification assigned to the study by the NCI. Inter-Group protocols should use the lead Groups protocol number.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: CCR CCMG approval of Released status 3/17/2004.  CDE supports DICOM Standard PS 3 - 204.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Patient Identifier
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The unique numeric or alphanumeric identification assigned to a participant in a clinical trial or research study.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: 05/25/2016 wz added NWU CS/CSI.5/18/16 jk moved to MCL context CSIs. 3/7/16 jk added MCL Clinical CSI. 12/11/14 jc added Exceptional Responder CSI. 12/10/14 jc added CDUS Rave Integration CSI.  CDE supports DICOM Standard PS 3 - 2004. v4.0 replaces v3.0 to use a version VD that increases max length from 12 to 20 characters

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Body Weight in Kilograms
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Measurement of an individual's weight in kilograms.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: CDE supports DICOM Standard PS 3 - 2004

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Person Height Measurement
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Value for an individual's height measured in centimeters.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Patient Subgroup Assignment
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Subgroup assignment given to a participant on a protocol.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Replaces v4.0 with a new version of the VD with extended field length from 10 to 40 characters.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Registering Group
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Name of the practice group where the patient was originally registered on study.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Registering Institution Identification Code
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Code that uniquely identifies the institution where the research participant was registered in a clinical trial.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: 05/25/2016 wz added NWU CS/CSI.5/18/16 jk moved from EDRN to MCL context CSI.  3/7/16 jk added MCL Clinical CSI.7/20/2016 Removed ' [Manually-curated]' from CDE definition, wz.
DataElementQueryResults.administrativeNotes: 02.13.23_Set Reg Status to Standard for all CDISC Aligned content_ghd

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Country Code
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Two character coded value to represent a collective generic term "Country", referring to a wide variety of dependencies, areas of special sovereignty, uninhabited islands, and other entities in addition to the traditional countries.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Version 4.0 includes enumerated VD from CTEP with all permissible country codes from CTEP. Versioned to use latest version of VD. mc

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Payment Method
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Primary payer/insurance carrier information at the time of treatment on a protocol.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Versioned to use new version DEC. mc 11/8/19

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Disease Stage TNM
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: TNM value used to express the extent of a cancer within the body, citing disease extent in the primary tumor (T), lymph nodes (N), and metastatic sites (M).
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: TNM added to preferred name to differentiate from Numeric values.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Disease CDUS Code
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The unique number assigned to a disease based on Clinical Data Update System (CDUS) Disease Coding.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Histology/Cytopathology Description
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The free-text description of a histological and/or cytopathological type present in a pathology specimen, commonly referred to as the diagnosis.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Histologic Confirmation Date
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The date when a pathologic diagnosis is verified and confirmed.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: CCR CCMG approval of Released status on 1/7/2004.
DataElementQueryResults.administrativeNotes: 2022.11.15 AQT added for ticket request CADSR0001697. ak

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Informed Consent Version
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The version of the consent document in which the patient acknowledged participation on the protocol by signing the document.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: 05/25/2016 wz added NWU CS/CSI.New version created to replaced retired VD.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Zubrod Performance Status Score
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The functional level of the patient based on the Zubrod performance scale.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: 12/10/14 jc added CDUS Rave Integration CSI.  New version uses semantically complete and versioned DEC.  Standard registration status approved by VCDE 5/17/2005.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Enrollment Treatment Study Assignment Code
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Code delivered at the time of patient enrollment onto a clinical trial to denote the treatment assignment.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Prior Therapy Type Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Yes or No response to signify if a patient received any of the prior therapy treatment.
DataElementQueryResults.administrativeNotes: 11/16/23 Added alt OID for CCTG ticket number CADSR0003085 cjl; 12/21/22 added AQT for ticket request CADSR0001818 cjl;

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Administration Schedule Term Name
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The frequency schedule used for administration of agents.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: v4.0 uses a VD version that removes many legacy permissible values, approved by NCI CCR.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Dose Amount Unit of Measure Name
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Text name to represent the quantity or dosage of an agent administered to a patient/participant as part of a prior therapy record.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Version 6.0 expands max field from 16 to 30 characters maximum as requested for NCI-INC0282787-Theradex UOM 5.31.18 mc

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Best Response Assessment Type
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The best improvement achieved throughout the entire course of protocol treatment.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: New version 4.0 uses new version of VD.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Prior Therapy Type Text Code
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: One or two character representation(s) for type(s) of prior therapy modality (Chemotherapy, Immunotherapy, others) received by a patient/participant.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Value Domain is not correct for this DE.  Replaced by another CCR CDE.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Radiation Therapy Type
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Type of radiation therapy being used.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Assessment Findings Text
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Description of the findings from a procedure.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: New version uses versioned VD with expanded field length from 24 to 100.  Curated for NCI CCR clinical trial.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Treatment Start Date
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Begin date of a measure, procedure or agent.
DataElementQueryResults.administrativeNotes: 01.17.2024 Added AQT per request ticket CADSR0003292_mmt

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Stop Date
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The final or last day of a measure, procedure or agent.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: CCR CCMG approval of Released status on 1/7/2004.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Total Daily Dose Value
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Value to represent the total dose administered of an agent within one day.
DataElementQueryResults.administrativeNotes: 2022.9.30 AQT added for ticket request CADSR0001559. ak

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Checklist Number
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Unique identifer for each protocol eligibility checklist associated with a protocol; each successive versions or amendments of a study will have a checklist/checklist number associated with it.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Effective Date
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The date of approval of eligibility criteria by NCI.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Waiver Number
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The numeric identifier for a sponosor-granted waiver.  Not applicable for NCI sponsored studies.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Discussed in CCR CCMG on 1/28/2004.  CCR CCMG approval of Released status for non CTEP-sponsored trials.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Eligibility Checklist
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Response (Yes, No, or Not Applicable) to each item (question) on a protocol eligibility checklist for patient/participant enrollment.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: 05/25/2016 wz added NWU CS/CSI.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Adverse Event Onset Date
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The date when a symptom or Adverse Event (AE) initially occurred.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: CCR CCMG approval of Released status on 12/17/2003.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Adverse Event Description Text
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The qualitative description of an adverse event based on a verbatim report, or to qualify a response of 'other' from a list of adverse events.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Common Toxicity Criteria Attribution Code
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: A scale of values to indicate the causal relation between the treatment modality and the specific adverse event.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Disease Related Symptom Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no/unknown question that asks whether a symptom or adverse event is related to disease. [Manually-curated]
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: New version of CDE to replace text codes with full text indicators.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Previously Irradiated Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Yes/No/Unknown response to signifity that a lesion or site of disease has previously been irradiated.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Measurable/Non-Measurable
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Indicator of whether a lesion or site of disease is measurable or nonmeasurable.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: 5/6/15 removed from RECIST CRF CSI and All Mandatory CDE CSI. jc  3/20/15 removed candidate status; CDE 4749031 created for RECISTv1.1 CDE set. jc 8/13/13 added to RECISTv1.1 CRF CSI. jc

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Followed For Response Ind
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: A Yes/No/Unknown indicator that denotes if a subject can be evaluated for response (to protocol treatment).
DataElementQueryResults.origin: RECIST:Response Evaluation Criteria in Solid Tumors
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: CCR CCMG approved Released status on 11/19/2003.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Measurement Method Procedure Name
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Brief description of how a lesion measurement was determined.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Measurement X in Centimeters
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Measurement of a lesion/tumor or location in the "X" (first or length) dimension in centimeters; this is the longest measurement or largest value if only one measurement is captured.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Lesion Evaluation Number
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Sequential number corresponding to an evaluation timepoint.  (O for the baseline evaluation, 1 for the first evaluation, 2 for the second evaluation, etc.)

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Evaluation Code
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Code to follow the response of a specific non-measurable lesion, as specified at the time of each evaluation.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Comment Change From Baseline Text
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Comment text in reference to a change from baseline measurements.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Lab Collection Time
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The time when  a sample for a lab test was collected.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Reused existing CDE for Lab CRF. Classified with Standard CRF 4/2009. mc

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Course Number
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Number of the course (cycle) of treatment the patient received.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: CCR CCMG approval of Released status on 1/7/04.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Lot Number
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Lot number for the drug supply

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Access Route of Administration Text Code
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: A  text code or name to represent an access route for the administration of agents or substances.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Replaces v5.0 w/extended max field length. Permissible value of 'oral' (po) and alternate question text requested per 3/10/2010 request of G. Diaz.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Course Start Date
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The begin date for a course (cycle) of a protocol.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: CCR CCMG approval of Released status on 1/7/2004.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Arm
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Protocol-specific arm assignment identified in a formal communication.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Previous Dose Change Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Indicator of whether the patient dose was changed from the dose given in the prior course (cycle), and if the change was planned or unplanned.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Response Assessment Type
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The patient's disease state as of the last day of the observation period for the course (cycle).
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Uses new version VD.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Response Date
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Date of the evaluation used to determine the patient's disease status within a period of protocol time.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: CCR CCMG approval of Released status on 12/17/2003.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Toxicity Event Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Yes/No indication of whether toxicity occurred during a specific course (cycle) or phase of protocol activity.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: New version adds OC/Prop concepts to DEC. mc

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Case Report Form Type
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Abbreviated term to identify a data collection instrument (CRF) designed to record all of the clinical study-required information stipulated in the protocol to be reported to the sponsor on each trial subject.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Created to support build of Theradex CRFs in caDSR and in Rave

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Off Study Date
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The date when the patient/participant is removed from the protocol, i.e., is not being followed and will not be retreated.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: CCR CCMG approval of Released status on 10/22/2003.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Off Study Reason Code
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Coded reason the patient/participant is removed from a clinical trial, using an enumerated set of values used in CTMS reporting.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Replaces v3.0 with updated PV "Death" value meaning

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Best Response Date
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Date of the evaluation used to determine the patient's maximum improvement in disease status within a period of protocol time.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Relapse Date
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The date of the evaluation or procedure used to determine progressive disease after the establishment of a complete response (CR).
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: CCR CCMG approval of Released status on 12/17/2003.
DataElementQueryResults.administrativeNotes: 2022.9.30 AQT added for ticket request CADSR0001559. ak

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Course Disposition
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Status of a course (cycle) of treatment.  A "completed" course (cycle) is one which has been conducted in accordance with the protocol with respect to length (two day variance allowed). A course (cycle) is regarded as "discontinued" if it was shorter than specified in the protocol.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: National Cancer Institute Institute Code
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: A unique alpha-numeric code assigned by NCI to institution where the patient/participant was originally registered on study (institution where the patient signed the informed consent form). The code is assigned to protocol/records to identify the institution(s) participating in NCI-sponsored clinical trials and investigator records to identify address location.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Cause of Death at Autopsy
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Cause of death as confirmed by autopsy.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Resolved Date
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The date when an Adverse Event (AE) is resolved or returns to baseline value, based on standardized criteria (CTCAE).
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: CCR CCMG approval of Released status on 12/17/2003.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Infection Type
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: A succinct description of the infection (UTI, pneumonia, etc.)
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: 11.19.2020 Versioned to add concept annotation to DEC and VMs for NCI-INC0538950 20C0070 Curation and import_02 request. mc

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Infectious Agent Name
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Name of an infectious agent or microorganism obtained from culture or other testing, using an enumerated set of values.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: CCR CCMG approval of Released status 9/2003.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Infection Treatment Agent Text Name
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Text name for therapy or intervention targeting the infectious disease/condition under investigation.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Includes expanded max field length.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Adverse Event Infection Outcome
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Text description of the outcome of an infecious episode or event.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Page Number
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Number of the page of the case report form (CRF) referenced.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Common Toxicity Criteria Adverse Event Grade
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Adverse Event numeric grade (0-5) based on the NCI Common Toxicity Criteria.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: CDE value domain changed from numeric to character, Preferred name revised 11/19/03.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Form Completion Date
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The date on which a data capture form (CRF or case report form) was completed.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: 10/30/20 jk added Normal Tissue CSI.  10/12/20 jk  added Solid tumor CSI. 7/23/20 jk added BLCA Path CSIs.   Standard Registration Status on completion of caBIG community 30 day balloting process, October 30, 2009.
DataElementQueryResults.administrativeNotes: 02.13.23_Set Reg Status to Standard for all CDISC Aligned content_ghd

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Laboratory Finding Test Name
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Identifier name given to a test performed on body fluid(s) and tissues; test names are typically comprised of the analyte name, properties (%, Ratio, etc.), the type of body fluid tested, and any special instructions.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Version 6.0 replaces v5.0 with a versioned VD that increases the max field length from 120 to 200 characters.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Lab Unit of Measure Name
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The actual unit of measure for laboratory test results.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: New version includes versioned VD with corrected value meaning/value meaning description.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Result
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Text description of a procedure result.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Patient Age Value
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Age at the time of study enrollment, expressed in number of years completed at the last birthday.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: v3.1 removes 'CTMS' from short name of CDE.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Karnofsky Performance Status Score
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Score from the Karnofsky Performance status scale, representing the functional capabilities of a person.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: New version uses versioned DEC that is sematically complete.  Standard registration status approved by VCDE 5/17/2005. 3/24/2017 added alt question text for CTSP task, wz.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Waiver Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: A yes/no/NA indicator to denote if a subject's enrollment/eligibility requirements were waived for a sponsor-approved reason.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Discussed in CCR CCMG.  CCR CCMG approval of Released status for non CTEP-sponsored trials on 1/28/2004.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Concomitant Agent Concomitant Intervention or Procedure Reason
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The reason for administration of a concomitant (nonstudy) agent or measure.   This is not the pharmacologic classification of an agent (antibiotic, analgesic, etc.), but the reason for its administration to the patient. [Manually-curated]
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: New version uses VD with extended field length and permissible values.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Procedure Name
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Text name assigned to a health care procedure done for diagnostic, surveillance, treatment, palliation, or study-directed purposes.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Medical History Description
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Brief description of major medical and surgical events that occurred during the patient's lifetime.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: CCR CCMG approval of Released status 11/14/2003.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Finding Result Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Response represents summary findings for the evaluation of a body system/site as normal (N), abnormal (A), not examined (X), or other enumerated values.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Retired due to change in needs. dmr 5/29/2015 Changed back to released for use in C3D to Rave transition. mc 9.26.19

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Dose Limiting Toxicity Description
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Description of dose limiting toxicities for a drug or agent.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Corrected Aliquot Counter per Minute Number
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Numeric value for counter per minute for the aliquot adjusted to a reference time and corrected for background, crossover.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Sample ID Number
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Set of numbers used to unqiuely identify a sample/specimen.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: 12/11/14 jc added Exceptional Responder CSI.  New version incorporates longer maximum field length VD.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Tissue Class
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Classification of tissue as Normal or Tumor.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Sample Description Text
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Text description of a sample or specimen.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: 10/21/20 jk removed MCL CSI reuse.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Gamma Scan Positive Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The question that asks whether the lesion was seen, or was equivocal in appearance on a gamma scan for taken-up radionuclide.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Radiation Therapy Schedule
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Set of character terms to capture the frequency or schedule for the administration of an agent or measure.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Versioned to replace retired VD. mc

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Surgery Date
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The date of a surgical procedure.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: CCR CCMG approval of Released status on 1/7/2004.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Anatomic Site Name
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Text name of an anatomic organ site (single) within the body; may be referenced in primary site of disease, surgical intervention, or extent of disease documentation.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: v3.0 replaces v2.0 with a versioned VD that increases the maximum field length from 30 to 50 characters.  v4.0 extends maximum field length from 50 to 120 characters.dr

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Eligibility Criteria Text
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The complete text of an individual question/criterion on the eligibility checklist of a protocol.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: 05/25/2016 wz added NWU CS/CSI.v4.0 replaces v3.0 of the CDE with extended maximum length from 200 to 1000 characters.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Eligibility Criteria Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Indicator (Yes/No/Not Applicable) that a patient/participant has met all eligiblity criteria successfully for enrollment in a clinical trial.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Eligibility Waiver Reason
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The reason that a subject is given a sponsor-approved waiver for meeting protocol-defined eligibility requirements.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Discussed in CCR CCMG 1/28/2004.  CCR CCMG approval of Released status on 1/28/2004 for nonCTEP-sponsored trials.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Residual Disease Extent
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The amount of residual disease at the conclusion of a treatment or surgical intervention.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Antibody Name
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Name of the antibody under review or investigation.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: CCR CCMG approval of Released status 1/7/2004. Versioned VD and moved to CCR to support new CDE version. mc

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: CT Scan Positive Ind
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: A Yes/No reponse to signify that a lesion or disease was seen on Computer Tomography (CT) scan.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Surgical Biopsy Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Indication of whether a lesion was biopsied or not.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Corrected Radioniclude Counter per Minute
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Numeric value to represent a corrected radionuclide dose.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: CDUS Therapy Number Code
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Numeric codes, using MedDRA version 9.0 codes and compliant with the CDUS (Clinical Data Update System), to represent types of therapy.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Version 4.0 implements MedDRA v9.0 codes in use by CTEP electronic reporting systems effective July 1, 2006.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Anatomic Organ Site Text
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Text name of site(s) within the body or a body organ.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Start Time
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The start time for the administration of an intervention, using a 24-hour clock time.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: CCR CCMG approval of Released status on 1/7/2004.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Dose Level
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Dose Level of an agent or medication, assigned to a protocol patient/participant.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Agent Actual Dose
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The total dose of study drug given to the patient in the time period encompassed by the duration.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Actual Dose Administered Unit of Measure Name
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Text name to represent units of measure used to describe dosages of a study-dictated agent or measure.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Version 6.0 expands max field from 16 to 30 characters maximum as requested for NCI-INC0282787-Theradex UOM 5.31.18 mc

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Time Duration Unit of Measure Code
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Text Unit of Measure (UOM) term to express the length of time of an event or activity.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Replaces v4.0 with new version VD in order to correct one PV; Permissible value 'SEC' in v4.0 changed to 'SC' in v5.0 to align with Theradex reporting requirement.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Response Note Text
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Free text field to capture details and reason for a response call.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Supports CTMS reporting requirements v. 3.02 and subsequent version.s

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Adverse Event Report Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The question that asks whether an Adverse Event Report was filed with the Institutional Review Board (IRB) and/or the National Cancer Institute (NCI) or sponsor.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Serious Adverse Event  Reason
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Reason that an Adverse Event is evaluated to be serious.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: CDE modified from numeric to character data type, Preferred name revised 11/19/03.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Adverse Event Action
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Action taken in response to an adverse event.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Adverse Event Therapy
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Therapy required to treat an adverse event.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Dose Limiting Toxicity Ind
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Indication (Y or N) of an Adverse event considered to be a dose-limiting toxicity

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Adverse Event Outcome
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Final status of the patient related to an adverse event.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Protocol Agent Name
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Name of a substance delivered to a patient/participant as part of a clinical trial regimen or plan.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: v2.0 uses more specific long name to extend use of CDE beyond CTMS trials, and to limit the inclusion of concomitant agents in this element.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Stop Time
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The stop time for the administration of an intervention.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: CCR CCMG approval of Released Status 1/7/2004.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: FACT-G Questionnaire Not Administered Reason Text Name

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: MENQOL Domain Score

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Wide Range Achievement Test 3 Percentile Value

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: California Verbal Learning Test Children's Version Recall Measure Name
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Text terms for measures of recall and contrast scores within the California Verbal Learning Test Children's Version (CVLT-C). CVLT-C provides a short, individually administered assessment  of the strategies and processes involved in learning and recall of  verbal material. Assessment is made in the context of an everyday event.  It measures both recall and recognition of words over a number of trials  and has been found to be sensitive to memory deficits resulting from a  variety of neurological conditions. It is designed for ages 5 through  16.

It is designed for ages 5 through  16.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Person Transplantation Risk Category

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Short Form Brief Pain Inventory Complete Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Text term to signify whether the Brief Pain Inventory short form, consisting of nine questions, has been completed.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Long Form Brief Pain Inventory Complete Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Text term to signify whether the Brief Pain Inventory long form, consisting of 32 questions, has been completed.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Curated for CCR protocol 3/2009.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Dermatology Life Quality Index Complete Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Text term to signify that the Dermatology Life Quality Index tool, with 10 items, was completed.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Curated for CCR protocol 3/2009.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Pain Assessment Visual Analog Scale Score
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Text term that an individual chooses to self-describe a feeling of pain.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Patient Global Change Impression Measurement Category
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Classificiation of the response of an individual to a question of how their status has changed since the start of the clinical trial/study.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Curated for CCR protocol 3/2009.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Protocol Ice Application Timepoint Category
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Text term to signify if an event(s) has/have occurred prior to or after the application of ice to an individual.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Curated for CCR protocol 3/2009.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Acute Graft Versus Host Disease Late Occurrence Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Text term to signify whether an individual has features of late acute Graft vs. Host Disease (GVHD), such as vomiting, diarrhea, erythematous skin.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Chronic Graft Versus Host Disease Diagnosis Severity Type
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Text term to describe the intensity or severity of chronic Graft vs. Host Disease (GVHD) organ involvement at the time of diagnosis.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Curated to support CCR Transplant study 08C0097.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Chronic Graft Versus Host Disease Skin Involvement Body Surface Area Value
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Numeric value to represent the percentage (%) of skin involvement in a chronic Graft vs. Host Disease (GVHD) assessment of an individual.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Curated to support CCR Transplant study 08C0097.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Chronic Graft Versus Host Disease Skin Ulcer Assessment Anatomic Site Specify
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Text description of the anatomic location of chronic Graft vs. Host Disease (GVHD) skin ulcer(s).
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Curated to support CCR Transplant study 08C0097.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Chronic Graft Versus Host Disease Skin Ulcer Size Longest Measurement Value
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Numeric value to represent the dimension of the largest ulceration lesion in an individual with chronic Graft vs. Host Disease (GVHD) as measured in centimeters.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Curated to support CCR Transplant study 08C0097.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Chronic Graft Versus Host Disease Eye Wetting Assessment Outcome
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Value to represent the number of millimeters of wetting per eye of an individual with chronic Graft vs. Host Disease (GVHD), or the alternative result of an eye wetting assessment.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Curated to support CCR Transplant study 08C0097.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Chronic Graft Versus Host Disease Oral Cavity Mucosa Change Category
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Text category to signify the intensity of changes in erythema, lichenoid or mucoceles in the oral cavity mucosa for an individual with chronic Graft vs. Host Disease (GVHD).
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Curated to support CCR Transplant study 08C0097.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Chronic Graft Versus Host Disease Oral Cavity Mucosa Ulcer Change Category
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Text classification of changes in oral mucosa lesions measured in an individual with chronic Graft vs. Host Disease (GVHD).
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Curated to support CCR Transplant study 08C0097.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Chronic Graft Versus Host Disease Oral Cavity Change Total Score
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Numeric value to represent the total score assigned for all mucosal changes in an individual with chronic Graft vs. Host Disease (GVHD).
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Curated to support CCR Transplant study 08C0097.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Chronic Graft Versus Host Disease Severity Score
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Numeric value that represents the global rating or score for the intensity or severity of an individual's chronic Graft vs. Host Disease (GVHD).
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Curated to support CCR Transplant study 08C0097.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Chronic Graft Versus Host Disease Severity Global Rating Score
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Numeric value to represent the health care provider's global score for severity of an individual's chronic Graft vs. Host Disease (GVHD) using a 0 to 10 point scale.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Curated to support CCR Transplant study 08C0097.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Past Month Chronic Graft Versus Host Disease Severity Global Rating Score
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Health Care Provider global rating score to describe the status of an individual with chronic Graft vs. Host Disease (GVHD) as compared to the previous month.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Curated to support CCR Transplant study 08C0097.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Patient Self-Report Chronic Graft Versus Host Disease Severity Symptom Score
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Numeric value to represent the result of a patient-reported assessment of the severity of chronic Graft vs. Host Disease (GVHD) symptoms that includes but is not limited to skin itching, mouth dryness, mouth pain, mouth sensitivity, skin and/or joint tightening and genital discomfort when measured on a ten (10) point scale (with '0' as none to '10' being as bad as the individual can imagine).
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Curated to support CCR Transplant study 08C0097.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Chronic Graft Versus Host Disease Patient Self-Report Main Eye Problem Text
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Text to describe the self-described main complaint of an individual with chronic Graft vs. Host Disease (GVHD) in regard to eyes.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Curated to support CCR Transplant study 08C0097.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Chronic Graft Versus Host Disease Patient Self-Report Main Eye Problem Score
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Numeric value to represent self-reported severity of eye symptoms for an individual with chronic Graft vs. Host Disease (GVHD) using a ten (10) point scale (with '0' being not at all severe to '10' being most severe).
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Curated to support CCR Transplant study 08C0097.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Chronic Graft Versus Host Disease Vulva Vagina Symptom Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Text term to signify any self-reported vulvovaginal symptoms such as burning, pain, or discomfort in the vagina, labia or vulva, or any discomfort or pain during sexual intercourse, in an individual with chronic Graft vs. Host Disease (GVHD).
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Curated to support CCR Transplant study 08C0097.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Chronic Graft Versus Host Disease Patient Self-Report Severity  Score
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Numeric value that represents the global rating or score for the self-reported intensity or severity of an individual's chronic Graft vs. Host Disease (GVHD).
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Curated to support CCR Transplant study 08C0097.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Chronic Graft Versus Host Disease Patient Self-Report Severity Global Rating Score
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Numeric value to represent the self-reported global score for severity of an individual's chronic Graft vs. Host Disease (GVHD) using a 0 to 10 point scale.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Curated to support CCR Transplant study 08C0097.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Past Month Patient Self-Report Chronic Graft Versus Host Disease Severity Global Rating Score
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Self-reported global rating score to describe the status of an individual with chronic Graft vs. Host Disease (GVHD) as compared to the previous month.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Curated to support CCR Transplant study 08C0097.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Patient Assessment Current Pain Score
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Numeric value to represent an individual's self-reported level of pain or discomfort at a specific point in time.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Acute Graft Versus Host Disease Resolution Prior Chronic Graft Versus Host Disease Onset Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Text term to signify whether acute graft versus host disease (aGVHD) resolved prior to the onset of chronic graft versus host disease (cGVHD).
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Curated to support CCR ETIB study.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Pulmonary Or Systemic Viral Infection Integer::90 Day Post Bone Marrow Transplant Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Text term to signify the presence of pulmonary infection or systemic viral infection in the first 90 days post bone marrow transplantation (BMT).
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Curated to support CCR ETIB study.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Pulmonary Or Systemic Viral Infection Integer::90 Day Post Bone Marrow Transplant Text
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Text to describe virus(es) identified in pulmonary infections or systemic infections diagnosed 90 days post bone marrow transplantation.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Curated to support CCR ETIB study.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Active Or Recurrent Cytomegalovirus Integer::90 Day Post Bone Marrow Transplant Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Text term to signify whether any cytomegalovirus (CMV) disease or evidence of reactivation occurred 90 days post bone marrow transplantation.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Curated to support CCR ETIB study.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Acute Graft Versus Host Disease Biopsy Proven Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Text term to signify biopsy-based verification of a diagnosis of acute Graft vs. Host Disease (GVHD).
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Curated to support CCR ETIB protocol.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Third National Health and Nutrition Examination Survey Computated Value Text
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: A computed value intended for use as a reference to interpret the results of pulmonary function tests/spirometry testing; the NHANES III value is a reference that is compared to the results of a subject's testing in order to derive percentage of expected values for pulmonary function testing.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Curated to support CCR use of C3D.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Lab Procedure Preference Unit of Measure Name
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Preferred unit of measure (UOM) for a laboratory test result, per NCI standards or per protocol specification.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Supports C3D lab test functionality.  Includes new version VD to correct a value meaning/value meaning description error in the previous VD version.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Acquired Immunodeficiency Syndrome Systemic Illness Stage
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Value to represent the extent of the deficiency of cellular immunity caused by the human immunodeficiency virus (HIV) as characterized by the occurrence of systemic illness and changes in overall health.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Curated for CCR Intramural trial. v2.0 replaces v1.0 with a Value domain and value set that have been reworked

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Acquired Immunodeficiency Syndrome Immune Stage
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Numeric value to represent the extent of the deficiency of cellular immunity caused by the human immunodeficiency virus (HIV) as characterized by change in CD4 count.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Curated for CCR Intramural trial.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Acquired Immunodeficiency Syndrome Tumor Stage
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Value to represent the extent of the deficiency of cellular immunity caused by the human immunodeficiency virus (HIV) as characterized by the occurrence and anatomic location of sites of disease.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Curated for CCR Intramural trial.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Past Month Incomplete Empty Bladder Occurrence AUA Symptom Assessment Score
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Numeric value to signify how often over the past month a person had a sensation of not emptying the bladder completely before urination was finished.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Curated for NCI CCR trial. The AUA Symptom Score is a measure of the American Urological Association.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Past Month Urinary Frequency Occurrence AUA Symptom Assessment Score
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Numeric value to signify how often over the past month a person had to urinate again less than 2 hours after he/she finished urinating.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Curated for NCI CCR trial. The AUA Symptom Score is a measure of the American Urological Association.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Past Month Intermittent Urination Occurrence AUA Symptom Assessment Score
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Numeric value to signify how often over the past month a person found he/he had to stop and start again several times during urination.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Curated for NCI CCR trial. The AUA Symptom Score is a measure of the American Urological Association.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Past Month Urinary Urgency Occurrence AUA Symptom Assessment Score
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Numeric value to signify how often over the past month a person has found it difficult to postpone urination due to urinary urgency.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Curated for NCI CCR trial. The AUA Symptom Score is a measure of the American Urological Association.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Past Month Weak Urination Occurrence AUA Symptom Assessment Score
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Numeric value to signify how often over the past month a person has noticed a weak urination stream.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Curated for NCI CCR trial. The AUA Symptom Score is a measure of the American Urological Association.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Past Month Push Urination Occurrence AUA Symptom Assessment Score
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Numeric value to signify how often over the past month a person had to push or strain to begin urination.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Curated for NCI CCR trial. The AUA Symptom Score is a measure of the American Urological Association.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Past Month Nocturia Frequency Score
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Numeric value to represent how often over the past month did a person get up to urinate from bedtime until the time he/she got up in the morning.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Curated for NCI CCR trial. The AUA Symptom Score is a measure of the American Urological Association.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Urinary System American Urological Association Symptom Assessment Total Score
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Numeric value for the compiled score of self-reported urinary system performance, function, quality, or ability as measured by the American Urological Association (AUA).
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Curated for NCI CCR trial. The AUA Symptom Score is a measure of the American Urological Association.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Quality of Life Urinary Symptom Score
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Text term to represent the subjective measurement of an individual's sense of well-being and ability to enjoy life in the presence of urinary symptoms.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Curated for NCI CCR trial. The AUA Symptom Score is a measure of the American Urological Association.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Sex Behavior Quality of Life Erection Confidence Past Integer::6 Month Assessment Score
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Numeric entry that describes a man's confidence that he can achieve and maintain an erection.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Curated for NCI CCR trial.  The SHIM is a tool to assess ED (Erectile Dysfunction) in males, and is based on a past six months assessment.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Sex Behavior Quality of Life Erection Sufficient Penetration Past Integer::6 Month Assessment Score
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Numeric entry that describes a man's assessment of how often his erections were sufficient for penetration.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Curated for NCI CCR trial.  The SHIM is a tool to assess ED (Erectile Dysfunction) in males, and is based on a past six months assessment.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Sex Behavior Quality of Life Erection Maintenance Past Integer::6 Month Assessment Score
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Numeric entry to describe a man's assessment of how often he is able to maintain an erection after penetration of his partner.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Curated for NCI CCR trial.  The SHIM is a tool to assess ED (Erectile Dysfunction) in males, and is based on a past six months assessment.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Sex Behavior Quality of Life Erection Maintenance Difficulty Past Integer::6 Month Assessment Score
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Numeric entry that describes a man's assessment of how often it was to maintain an erection to completion of intercourse.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Curated for NCI CCR trial.  The SHIM is a tool to assess ED (Erectile Dysfunction) in males, and is based on a past six months assessment.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Sex Behavior Quality of Life Sexual Intercourse Satisfaction Past Integer::6 Month Assessment Score
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Numeric entry that describes a man's assessment of how often attempted sexual intercourse was satisfatory..
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Curated for NCI CCR trial.  The SHIM is a tool to assess ED (Erectile Dysfunction) in males, and is based on a past six months assessment.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Sex Behavior Health Assessment  Total Score
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Numeric value to represent the composite score from responding to a number of questions to assess a man's sexual health.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Curated for NCI CCR trial. The SHIM is a tool to assess ED (Erectile Dysfunction) in males, and is based on a past six months assessment.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Peritoneal Carcinomatosis Stage
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Categorization of the extent of peritoneal carcinomatosis in the abdomen, using the Gilly Classification to describe the size and location of sites of disease.
DataElementQueryResults.origin: Gilly Classification: Gilly Classification published by Gilly et al., 1994, for the characterization of Peritoneal Carcinomatosis
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Created to support NCI CCR trial.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Protocol Agent Manufacturer Adverse Event Reporting Submission Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Text term to represent submission of expedited notification that a subject has experienced an adverse event to the manufacturer/producer of the therapeutic agent (drug, intervention therapy) used in a clinical trial protocol.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Curated to support NCI CCR protocol.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Graft Versus Host Disease Treatment With Immunosuppressive Therapy Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Text term to signify whether Graft vs. Host Disease (GVHD) was treated with agents or therapy to suppress the immune response.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Curated to support CCR Transplantation study.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Malignant Neoplasm At Chronic Graft Versus Host Disease Diagnosis Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Text term to signify whether a malignant disease was present at the time of chronic Graft vs. Host Disease (GVHD) was diagnosed.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Curated to support CCR Transplantation study.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Secondary Malignant Neoplasm At Chronic Graft Versus Host Disease Diagnosis Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Text term to signify whether a malignancy derived as a result of a primary condition was present at the time of chronic Graft vs. Host Disease (GVHD) diagnosis.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Curated to support CCR Transplantation study.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: HLA Antigens Crossmatch IncompatibilityType
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Text subdivision to signify the type of human leukocyte antigen (HLA) matching Incompatibility was detected during HLA typing..
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Curated to support CCR Transplantation study.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Infection Integer::90 Day Post Bone Marrow Transplantation Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Text term to signify whether an infection occurred within 90 days after a bone marrow transplantion occurred.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Curated to support CCR Transplantation study.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Engraftment Syndrome Symptom Present Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Text term to signify the presence of symptoms of marrow engraftment such as fever, rash, or pulmonary deterioration became evident after a bone marrow transplantation.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Curated to support CCR Transplantation study.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Bone Marrow Transplantation Within Integer::90 Day Occurrence Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Text term to signify whether a disease relapse occurred within 90 days following a bone marrow transplantation procedure.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Curated to support CCR Transplantation study.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: PSA Doubling Time Month Duration Number
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Number to represent the calculation result of the time in months required for a PSA (Prostate Specific Antigen) value to double in value.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: PSA Increase Slope Monthly Rate
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Numeric value to represent the rate of rise in the PSA (Prostate Specific Antigen) level per month expressed as ng/mL.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: PSA Velocity Increase Monthly Rate
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Number to represent the calculated result of the monthly rate of increase in PSA (Prostate Specific Antigen) levels in succeeding PSA tests, expressed as ng/mL per month.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Person Post Intervention Biological Response Occurrence Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Text description of the type of biological response achieved by a person after an intervention.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Curated to support CCR trial in C3D

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Person Comorbidity Condition Name
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Text term to identify a coexistent disease or condition in a person.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Text term to signify a completed assessment using the Manual Ability Measure-36 Assessment (MAM-36), a rating scale of 36 everyday tasks that measures self-reported manual ability.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Manual Ability Measure-36 Assessment Complete Date
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Calendar date of a completed assessment using the Manual Ability Measure-36 (MAM-36), a rating scale of 36 everyday tasks that measures self-reported manual ability.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Curated for NCI CCR Protocol in C3D.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Manual Ability Measure-36 Assessment Result Measure Score
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Numeric value for a score on the Manual Ability Measure-36 (MAM-36), a rating scale of 36 everyday tasks that measures self-reported manual ability.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Manual Ability Measure-36 Assessment Result Total Score
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Numeric value to represent the total score for the Manual Ability Measure-36 Assessment (MAM-36), a rating scale of 36 everyday tasks that measures self-reported manual ability.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Jebsen-Taylor Hand Function Test Assessment Complete Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Text term to signify the status of a Jebsen-Taylor Hand Function Test Assessment, a seven part test that evaluates a broad range of hand functions used in daily activities using common items such as cans, paper clips, and pencils.

It features 25 key-style pegs with holes in various positions in space, and is especially good for testing lateralized brain damage.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Grooved Pegboard Test Assessment Complete Date
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Calendar date of a completed assessment using the Grooved Pegboard test, a manipulative dexterity test using a pegboard device with five rows of five holes.  It features 25 key-style pegs with holes in various positions in space, and is especially good for testing lateralized brain damage.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Curated for NCI CCR Protocol in C3D.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Grooved Pegboard Test Assessment Right Hand Result Time Value
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Time measured in seconds for the completion of a task that is part of the Grooved Pegboard Test using the right hand.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Grooved Pegboard Test Assessment Left Hand Result Time Value
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Time measured in seconds for the completion of a task that is part of the Grooved Pegboard Test using the left hand.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Total sum of time measured in seconds for the completion of tasks that are part of the Grooved Pegboard Test using the right hand.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Total sum of time measured in seconds for the completion of tasks that are part of the Grooved Pegboard Test using the left hand.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Curated for NCI CCR Protocol in C3D.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Disabilities of the Arm Shoulder and Hand Outcome Measure Assessment Complete Date
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Calendar date for a completed assessment using the Disabilities of the Arm Shoulder and Hand Outcome Measure (DASH), a 30-item, self-reported questionnaire designed to measure physical and social function along with symptom impact associated with musculosketetal disorders of the upper limb.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Curated for NCI CCR Protocol in C3D.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Assessment of Motor and Process Skills Assessment Complete Date
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Calendar date of a completed assessment using the Assessment of Motor and Process Skills Assessment (AMPS), an observational assessment that is used to measure the quality of a person's activities of daily living (ADL); the quality of the person's ADL performance is assessed by rating the effort, efficiency, safety, and independence of 16 ADL motor and 20 ADL process skill items.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Electrocardiographic Finding QTcB Assessment Result Time in Millisecond Number
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: A formula-based value which takes into account the physiologic shortening of the QT interval which occurs as the heart rate increases, permitting comparison of the QT interval across a range of rates. It is mathematically defined as: QTcB = QT/SqRootRR(seconds) and theoretically corrects the QT interval to that which would be observed at a heart rate of 1 cycle per second.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Curated to support NCI CCR clinical trial

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Electrocardiographic Finding QTcF Assessment Result Time in Millisecond Number
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: A formula-based value which takes into account the physiologic shortening of the QT interval which occurs as the heart rate increases, permitting comparison of the QT interval across a range of rates. It is mathematically defined as: QTcF = QT/CubeRootRR(seconds) and theoretically corrects the QT interval to that which would be observed at a heart rate of 1 cycle per second
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Curated to support NCI CCR clinical trial
